# Project Conventions

Conventions for this codebase. Follow them when adding or modifying code.

## Project Layout

```
convert-compress/
├── App/              # App entry point, commands, window config
├── Assets/           # Static visual assets (icons)
├── Assets.xcassets/  # Asset catalogs
├── Core/
│   ├── Constants/    # App-wide constants (AppConstants, StorageKeys, ResizeConstants)
│   ├── Logging/      # Central AppLogger namespace
│   └── Models/       # Value-type domain models (structs/enums only)
├── Processing/       # Image pipeline (CIImage-based)
│   └── Encoder/      # CustomImageEncoder implementations
├── Services/         # Singletons & stateful coordinators (one folder per service)
├── Shaders/          # Metal shaders
├── StoreKit/         # StoreKit configuration
├── Theme/
│   ├── Components/   # Reusable view components, grouped by category
│   └── Utils/        # Theme-related helpers
├── Utils/            # Stateless, reusable, non-UI helpers
├── ViewModels/       # @MainActor @Observable/ObservableObject VMs; split via extensions
└── Views/            # SwiftUI views, scoped to features
```

## File Naming

- One type per file, named after the primary type: `Foo.swift` contains `struct Foo` (or closely related helpers in a `// MARK: -` section).
- ViewModel partials: `ImageToolsViewModel+<Concern>.swift`. The concern must match the actual responsibility (e.g. `+Export`, not `+Processing`).
- Views follow block/feature/control nesting: `Views/<Feature>/Blocks/...` for layout blocks; `Views/<Feature>/Controls/...` for interactive controls; each control lives under its own folder when it has more than one file.
- Test files in `convert-compress-tests/` mirror source layout.

## Architecture

- `@MainActor @Observable` for new state containers; retain `ObservableObject` where already entrenched (`ImageToolsViewModel`).
- Prefer value types (`struct`, `enum`) for models. Services that own shared state may be `actor` or `@MainActor final class`.
- Inject dependencies explicitly. Singletons are reserved for truly app-wide services: `ImageIOCapabilities`, `SandboxAccessManager`, `PurchaseManager`, `PaywallCoordinator`, `RatingCoordinator`, `UsageTracker`, `PresetsStore`, `AppLogger`.
- Side-effectful operations run via `Task` with explicit priority. Avoid `DispatchQueue.main.async*` except where SwiftUI-adjacent debouncing is simpler; prefer the `Debouncer` utility for debouncing.
- Feature state machines: model as `enum` with associated values.

## UserDefaults / Persistence

All persisted keys go through `Core/Constants/StorageKeys.swift`. No literal string keys in feature code.

Namespace: `"<bundleIdentifier>.<feature>.<name>.v<version>"`, lowercase snake_case for `<feature>.<name>`. Bump the `v<version>` suffix when a key's schema changes.

Storage choices:
- `UserDefaults.standard` for local preferences and local-only state.
- `NSUbiquitousKeyValueStore.default` for iCloud-synced state (e.g., presets).

## Logging

Use `AppLogger` from `Core/Logging/AppLogger.swift`. Never use `print` for diagnostics.

```swift
AppLogger.ingestion.debug("…")
AppLogger.purchase.error("…")
```

Add new categories to `AppLogger` as the app grows. Categories are short, lower-case words (e.g. `ingestion`, `sandbox`, `purchase`, `presets`).

## Concurrency

- UI state mutations on `@MainActor`. Cross-actor hops: `await MainActor.run { … }`.
- Use `AsyncSemaphore` (in `Utils/`) for bounded concurrency.
- Use `Debouncer` (in `Utils/`) for any "wait X ms, then run" patterns. Do not recreate ad-hoc `DispatchWorkItem` debouncing.

## Error Handling

- Domain errors: dedicated `enum FooError: Error` in the same module as the consumer.
- Avoid `try?` at error-producing seams where the failure deserves a log.
- No force-unwraps (`!`) in production code except for well-known compile-time invariants (e.g. a constant `UTType` identifier used in multiple stable system paths). Document any exception.

## SwiftUI

- Keep `body` short; extract computed vars and small `@ViewBuilder` helpers.
- Reusable components live in `Theme/Components/<Category>/`.
- `@EnvironmentObject` only for app-global view models; `@Bindable` for `@Observable` coordinators; `@StateObject`/`@ObservedObject` for legacy `ObservableObject` use.
- Animation constants come from `Theme.Animations`; metrics from `Theme.Metrics`; colors from `Theme.Colors`; fonts from `Theme.Fonts`.

## Localization

- Every user-facing string uses `String(localized:)` with a stable default. Do not hardcode UI copy.

## Rule Maintenance

When introducing a new convention (folder, naming rule, pattern), update this file in the same change.
